<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>This is the adorable moment a dog responds to a grin and a thumbs up with a smile of his own.</p>

<p>Buddy, a six-year-old Bichon Frise, knows he gets a positive response when he shows his teeth, according to his owner. </p>

<p>Kelly Ellise Lockett took a video of Buddy as she sat with family in the garden of their home in Liverpool.</p>

<p>The 34-second-long clip shows the sweet white dog dressed up in a grey coat while sitting on an outdoor sofa.</p>

<p>Buddy, a six-year-old Bichon Frise, knows he gets a positive response when he shows his teeth, according to his owner</p>

<p>A man sitting next to the dog says 'Buddy, Buddy' to catch his attention before offering the dog two thumbs up and a huge smile.</p>

<p>Another man the other side of the dog nudges him and says 'smile', prompting the dog to show off his pearly whites.</p>

<p>His smile is even wider the second time and Kelly lets out a burst of laughter from behind the camera. </p>

<p>The 34-second-long clip shows the sweet white dog dressed up in a grey coat while sitting on an outdoor sofa</p>

<p>Kelly says 'cheese' as the group laugh along.</p>

<p>Dogs usually bar their teeth to show discomfort, but it could also be a sign of playfulness and excitement.   </p>

<p>Kelly said: 'Buddy responds to certain key words with a smile but Buddy smiles all the time. </p>

<p>'We all laugh at him every time and he knows it gets a positive response so he does it more.'</p>
